text:
Ivanna Rohashko (born 28 October 1996 in Dubno, Ukraine) living in Vila Real, Portugal is a Ukrainian-born Portuguese beauty pageant titleholder who was crowned Miss Intercontinental Portugal 2019 and Miss Earth Portugal 2020.
Personal life.
Rohashko was born in Dubno, Ukraine. She is a master’s student in gerontology holds a degree in psychomotor rehabilitation.
Miss Intercontinental Portugal 2019.
Rohashko was crowned Miss Intercontinental Portugal 2019 pageant.
Miss Intercontinental 2019.
Rohashko represented Portugal at the Miss Intercontinental 2019 pageant on December 20, 2019 in Egypt, but unplaced.
Miss Queen Portugal 2020.
Rohashko joined Miss Queen Portugal 2020 pageant on September 12, 2020, where she was crowned Miss Earth Portugal 2020. She replaced last year’s Miss Queen Portugal, Camila Vitorino, who has earlier this month renounces her title as Miss Earth Portugal due to professional reasons.
Miss Earth 2020.
Rohashko represented Portugal at Miss Earth 2020 on November 29, 2020 in the Philippines.
